  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Entity<MirrorId,Mirror>, EntityWithLifecycle<MirrorId,Mirror>, EventPlayer, VersionableEntity<MirrorId,Mirror>, WithLifecycle, EventReceiver, EventSubscriber

    public final class MirrorProjection
extends Projection<MirrorId,Mirror,MirrorVBuilder>
    The Mirror projection for domain aggregates.

    This entity belongs to the system context. It mirrors the state of an aggregate. Not every aggregate has a mirror projection. Refer to the MirrorRepository for more details.

    The projection defines an EntityColumn which stored the type URL of the state, which is mirrored.

    Implementation Note:
    Many subscriber methods of this class ignore their arguments. The argument of a subscriber method is an event used by the framework to bind the method to the event type. The content of the event, in those cases, is irrelevant.

      • getAggregateType

        public java.lang.String getAggregateType()
        Obtains the type of the mirrored aggregate state.

        This method defined an EntityColumn required for effective querying.

        The framework never queries for several types of mirrors in a single call. SPI users may exploit this fact when optimising databases for the system types.

        Returns:
        the state TypeUrl as a String
